ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: I will recommend to a student, but I recommend they know some basic knowledge about turbulence before taking this course since it's an advanced course.
I'd obviously recommend it for a student who wants to learn about turbulence. The course provides a thorough introduction to the field and can be tailored to individual student needs.
This course is tough since turbulence is tough. Highly recommended if you will study turbulence-relative research in the future.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: One part of my work is associated with turbulence, and I'm very excited to get to understand it in a quantitative way.
It was well-tailored to my research, and it basically gave me a crash course to be able to read papers in the field!
It gives me fundamental understanding about turbulence. Even though turbulence is so hard, Nich indeed explains it well to students.
